tip.text: Beautiful and serene place, worth a visit. Could be crowded in the afternoon but we had a pleasant stroll in the evening

formattedAddress: 右京区嵯峨小倉山田淵山町
location.address: 右京区嵯峨小倉山田淵山町

tip.text: The buffet brunch is very worth it. Have a nice meal on the weekend then head to the pool to chill / suntan / swim

venue.name: Starfish Bloo @ W Retreat & Spa Bali - Seminyak

tip.text: Come here during sunset for a drink to chill. Seats near the pool require a minimum spending. Personally think that the hype about this place is too much.
My travel partner enjoyed this meal thoroughly. We waited around 45 minutes as we arrived at 5.15pm for dinner. However I've waited for a longer time during the summer, good but not worth the wait.

formattedAddress: 右京区嵯峨天龍寺北造路町44-1 (天龍寺斜め向かい)
location.address: 右京区嵯峨天龍寺北造路町44-1

tip.text: Lovely place but very crowded. The zen temple was originally a villa of a shogun and is covered in gold leaf. An entrance fee is required to get in.
The donburi is amazing, Wagyu beef, Uni, caviar, foie gras topped with an onsen egg and shoya sauce. On the pricey end but come at lunch and they have a discount
Highly recommend this hotel. It is new with quality service and beautiful rooms. Enjoyed my stay here thoroughly, try the Chinese restaurant for delicious food.
This is authentic Japanese food, not your usual ramen or rice bowls. But healthy and well made okowa (traditional Japanese steamed rice). Will definitely try the kaiseiki meal one day
Our set dinner was amazing. The Uni soup as well as the fish was delicious. It is really worth the money. will definitely try the tasting menu when I come back to Makati
Get the Wildflour breakfast with the bacon steak! I'm coming back to try the ricotta pancakes for sure

formattedAddress: Ground Floor, V Corporate Center (Leviste Street)

tip.text: Great place to be on a Sunday morning! Took a walk around and bought some products from milea bath & body and had some light bites

formattedAddress: Legazpi Park, V. A. Rufino St (btwn Salcedo & Legazpi St)
location.address: Legazpi Park, V. A. Rufino St

tip.text: One of the prettiest pancake stacks I've ever seen. My partner enjoyed his breakfast too but not the Xmas mint latte
The view from the canopy is amazing
Drinking a cocktail in the pool bar. Drinks on the pricey end though
Unagi and tempura don 😋 so good washed down with a happy hour beer

formattedAddress: Suntec City Mall, Sky Garden, North Wing (3 Temasek Boulevard)
location.address: Suntec City Mall, Sky Garden, North Wing

tip.text: Brioche and mushrooms were too dry but the scrambled eggs, coffee were good
The char siew is amazing. I like the portion size here, not too much but just enough to have a good taste of each dish. My family likes it too

formattedAddress: #01/02-00 Thye Shan Mansion (325 New Bridge Rd)

tip.text: We like the Chilli crab Bao and the coffee here. A quiet space during the weekends like this is hard to come by
Like the concept, not too bad for a simple healthy meal but nothing memorable

formattedAddress: #02-20/22, Raffles City Shopping Centre (252 North Bridge Road)

tip.text: A hidden and quiet Japanese joint. Only tried the sashimi lunch  set so far. Will be back to try other things.
The perfect hidden find near my workplace. $4.90 (6 toppings on a base of lettuce) for a healthy salad - no seats so takeaway only
A quiet Sunday evening with this amazing cheese board, a couple of drinks and the view

formattedAddress: #06-01, National Gallery Singapore (1 St. Andrew's Road)

tip.text: Mushroom and herbed cheese with scrambled eggs? Amazing.
Hot and cold seafood platter and a glass of champagne on a Saturday night, ending off with fireworks just outside the restaurant. The wait for the table took quite a while though.
Lovely market on Saturday. Bought lots of handmade items, essential oils and had some food at the stalls. One of the nicer places in Sydney.

formattedAddress: Jack Mundey Pl. (Also Playfair & George Sts.)

tip.text: Absolutely lovely place for late morning tea. Had the tea for two set. It came with 4 scones, 6 finger sandwiches, 2 choices of jam, heavy cream and 2 pots of tea. The jam and scones were heavenly.
The cinnamon and Nutella cronuts are the the bomb
Incredible architectural design
Beautiful historical building. Shops aren't particularly attractive to us but worth a visit.

formattedAddress: 455 George St. (btwn Market St. & Druitt St.)

tip.text: Perfect for surfing, sun bathing or just chilling at the beach with friends and family. Close to the city but a great escape from the hustle and bustle.

formattedAddress: Queen Elizabeth Dr. (btwn Notts Ave. & Ramsgate Ave.)

tip.text: Good for a walk or a jog along the coast. Very scenic views and a nice escape from the city
Good photo spot for the iconic shot of the Harbour bridge and the opera house!
Took the tram around the gardens. $10 for adults, $5 for children. Really worth it for the guided tour and an overview of the place. After that we took a walk around and had a nice cuppa in the cafe.
The Rocks musuem, it's free! And there are markets here on weekends.
Intricately decorated and fine tasting cakes
Tasty and appetising soup in noodles
High tea on a weekend. Didn't book in advance so we sat outside in the alfresco area. The food came in a pretty tier and TWG tea was served. Great savoury bites especially the salmon canapés 👍🏼

formattedAddress: The Fullerton Bay Hotel (80 Collyer Quay)

tip.text: Back again for my waffle fix. Stout and chocolate 😋👍🏼
Not many choices. Personally don't think it's worth it
One of my favourite bars thanks to the amazing view. Dancefloor can get quite crowded on Fridays and the crowd has many foreigners.
One of the best omelettes I've eaten. Ordered it with Monterey Jack cheese, avocado and mushroom. Amazing with the toast👍🏼
Truffle beef bowl done right 😋 not sure why they always seem to be short on the menus and utensils haha. But a lovely cafe to have a meal with friends.
Love this place, had truffle fries, calamari, fresh coconut juice some chilled beer and wine. Lazing here on a Sunday afternoon/evening is amazing. It's a dog friendly place too!
Only 3 types choices of menu for dinner. Enjoyable experience but only for special occasions.
A nice hike to the peak. Wasn't too difficult but don't hike when it rains, ground would be slippery
Cosy cafe with staff that put effort into each cup they make. Had a nice coffee with pastry here in the morning.

The room is amazing, high ceilings, clean and spacious bathroom, free device with Internet access. The lounge is available 24 hours to patrons and the service staff is good. Overall a great stay here!

tip.text: Came here on a Saturday morning. Didn't have to wait as the place was very spacious. Authentic push cart dim sum place full of locals but I would say just an ok meal.

location.address: 2/F, Low Block, Hong Kong City Hall, 5 Edinburgh Pl

tip.text: Had the cheese noodles with cheese fishballs, it was good! Couldn't finish one portion since it was too rich, heard the pork cheek is delicious but didn't try it.
